refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
voidlibxml_set_streams_context resourcecontext
Sets the streams context for the next libxml document load or write.

&reftitle.parameters;
context
The stream context resource (created with stream_context_create)

&reftitle.errors;

 Throws a TypeError when a non-stream resource is
 passed to context.

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    8.4.0

     libxml_set_streams_context now throws a
     TypeError when a non-stream resource is passed
     to context, instead of throwing later when the
     context is used.

  &reftitle.examples;



    A libxml_set_streams_context example


<?php

$opts = array(
    'http' => array(
        'user_agent' => 'PHP libxml agent',
    )
);

$context = stream_context_create($opts);
libxml_set_streams_context($context);

// request a file through HTTP
$doc = DOMDocument::load('http://www.example.com/file.xml');

?>
